               <head>BEDE, HAIMO, JOACHIM OF FIORE; S. XIV in. </head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1–32)</locus>
                     <author key="person_61539765">BEDE</author>
                     <title key="work_955">Commentary on the Canonical Epistles</title>
                     <rubric>Incipit prologus uenerabilis Bede presbiteri super septem canonicas epistolas.</rubric>
                     <incipit><supplied>I</supplied>acobus, Petrus, Iohannes, Iudas, septem epistolas ediderunt </incipit>
                     <explicit> sed ante omne seculum et nunc et in omnia s. s. amen.</explicit>
                     <note><ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=CPL&amp;number=1362"><title>CPL</title> 1362</ref>; <title>CCSL</title> 121 (1983), pp. 179–342.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2">
                     <locus>(fols. 32–133)</locus>
                     <author key="person_79148266">HAIMO OF AUXERRE</author>
                     <title key="work_1944">Commentary on the Apocalypse</title>
                     <rubric>Incipit epithoma succincte expositionis super librum Apocalipsis. </rubric>
                     <incipit><supplied>L</supplied>egimus in ecclesiastica historia beatum Iohannem a Domiciano impiissimo Cesare in Pathmos insula relegatum exilio </incipit>
                     <explicit> et in gratia terminum poneret. </explicit>
                     <finalRubric>Explicit Haymo super Apocalipsim.</finalRubric>
                     <note><title>PL</title> 117. 937–1220; Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 3072, 3122.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3">
                     <locus>(fols. 133–4)</locus>
                     <author key="person_78749939">IOACHIM OF FIORE</author>
                     <title key="work_7094">De Septem Sigillis</title>
                     <incipit><supplied>S</supplied>ub hoc tempore continetur de Abraham Ysaac et Iacob </incipit>
                     <explicit> in ea gaudium sempiternum amen.</explicit>
                     <note>Ed. M. Reeves and B. Hirsch-Reich, <title>RTAM</title> 21 (1954), 239–47; copies, not this one, listed in Reeves, <title>The Influence of Prophecy in the Later Middle Ages</title> (Oxford, 1969), p. 515.</note>
                  </msItem>
