                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1700" notBefore="1600">
                        <p>Standard Merton s. xvii; sewn on five bands; formerly chained from the usual position. Fols. i-ii, 135–6 are paper binding leaves, the outermost from the same printed book as in MS 45. On fol. 134 are marks of two clasps and of the large iron chain-staple.</p>
